# 📄 Product Requirements Document (PRD)  
**Project:** 9point75 Woodworks LLC Website  
**Owner:** Russ / 9point75 Woodworks LLC  
**Target Launch:** April 30  

---

## 1. 🎯 Objective
Design and launch a high-converting website that:
- Attracts home & furniture clients
- Generates custom quote requests
- Positions the brand as high-end, handcrafted, and professional

---

## 2. 👤 Target Audience
- Homeowners seeking custom furniture or cabinetry
- Clients interested in heirloom-quality pieces
- Budget range: $200 – $25,000 (position toward higher-end)
- Geographic focus: Northeastern North Carolina (primary) + travel/delivery available

---

## 3. 💎 Value Proposition
- Fully custom, one craftsman from start to finish
- High-touch client experience:
  - Consultation → Design → Build → Delivery
- Ongoing client involvement:
  - Design iterations
  - Progress updates/photos
- Premium materials:
  - Hardwoods: Walnut, White Oak, Maple
  - Exotics: Purpleheart, Padauk, Mahogany

---

## 4. 🧱 Core Features

### 4.1 Homepage
- Text-driven (value-first messaging)
- Minimal, clean hero section
- Sections:
  - Brand positioning / headline
  - Process overview
  - Featured work (broad categories)
  - Trust signals (Veteran-owned, handcrafted)
  - Subtle CTA (Request a Quote)

---

### 4.2 Gallery (Portfolio)
Organized by category:
- Cabinetry / Built-ins
- Furniture
- Military Shadowboxes / Gifts
- Plaques
- Other

Format:
- Image-based (no detailed project pages at launch)

---

### 4.3 About Page
- Personal story
- Craftsmanship philosophy
- Veteran-owned positioning (secondary emphasis)

---

### 4.4 Quote Request Form (Primary Conversion)
Fields:
- Name
- Email
- Phone
- Project type
- Budget range
- Timeline
- Description
- Measurements
- Location
- File/image uploads (inspiration)

---

### 4.5 How It Works Section
1. Inquiry  
2. Consultation  
3. Design Iteration  
4. Build Process  
5. Delivery + Walkthrough  

---

### 4.6 Contact
- Email: 9point75Woodworks@gmail.com
- No public address
- Appointment-only messaging

---

### 4.7 Social Links
- Facebook
- Instagram  
(links only, no embeds)

---

## 5. 🎨 Design Direction

### Style
- Primary: Handcrafted
- Secondary: Professional / Luxury
- Accent: Subtle rugged tone

### UX Direction
- Traditional structure
- Clean, fast, no animations
- Subtle CTAs

---

## 6. 🧠 Content Strategy
- Text-led homepage
- Subtle education on craftsmanship and value
- No blog or content hub

---

## 7. 📈 Conversion Strategy
- Primary CTA: Request a Quote
- Light pricing guidance
- Trust builders:
  - Veteran-owned
  - Handcrafted
  - Transparent process

---

## 8. 🚫 Out of Scope (Phase 2+)
- E-commerce
- Detailed project pages
- Blog/content marketing
- Advanced filtering

---

# ⚙️ Technical Specification

## 1. 🧩 Platform Choice
Recommended: Webflow

### Why:
- Easy updates
- Strong design control
- Fast performance
- CMS-ready for expansion

---

## 2. 🏗️ Architecture

### Pages
- Home
- About
- Gallery
- Contact / Quote Form

---

### CMS Collections
- Gallery Items:
  - Category
  - Images
  - Title (optional)

---

## 3. 📬 Form Handling
- Webflow forms (or Zapier/Make integration)
- Email notifications to:
  - 9point75Woodworks@gmail.com

Optional:
- Store submissions in Airtable / CMS

---

## 4. 🌐 SEO Basics
- Keywords:
  - “Custom furniture North Carolina”
  - “Custom cabinets NC”
- Include:
  - City + State
  - Service region
- Proper heading structure
- Image alt tags

---

## 5. ⚡ Performance
- No heavy animations
- Compressed images
- Fast load speeds

---

## 6. 🔐 Security & Hosting
- SSL enabled
- CDN-backed hosting (Webflow or equivalent)

---

## 7. ✏️ Editing Capabilities

Client can:
- Upload/remove images
- Update text
- Add gallery items

Restricted:
- Layout/structure

---

## 8. 🔮 Future Expansion
- E-commerce
- Case studies
- Testimonials
- Lead automation

---

